--- !u!114 &3438553711231360354
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 6953650608404046062}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "In such scenarios, there are two (2) clauses to determine the state of
    an object, as seen in the opposite. If forces are balanced, the object will remain
    in its current state. Going back to the previous example, since both objects
    are at rest, then all forces are balanced. But, since motion was introduced,
    there was an imbalance between the two. As a result, the man began to fall forward.
    Oftentimes, there is also a change in state when one object is moving in one
    direction, but an external force keeps on changing the object\u2019s direction.
    The followig is a simple analysis to determine the state of an object."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_fontSharedMaterials: []
  m_fontMaterial: {fileID: 0}
  m_fontMaterials: []
  m_fontColor32:
    serializedVersion: 2
    rgba: 4278190080
  m_fontColor: {r: 0, g: 0, b: 0, a: 1}
  m_enableVertexGradient: 0
  m_colorMode: 3
  m_fontColorGradient:
    topLeft: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
