  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Newton\u2019s First Law, the Law of Inertia, states that an object will
    remain in its current state unless there is a change in its equilibrium caused
    by an unbalanced, outside force.\n\nIn the given definition, equilibrium is stated.
    Equilibrium is simply balance. The state of an object\u2019s equilibrium is known
    as its inertia (Latin, inactive). Inertia is best defined as the resistance of
    an object to change its state of motion.\n\nSuppose we have a man pushing a car
    which has an engine problem, with two passengers (see below). The car, from its
    initial speed of 0 m/s, revved up to 80 m/s in just 6 seconds. The man, who was
    struggling to push, was at a state of rest."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
